104808713:
The tragic incident in Hanumangarh, Rajasthan involved a head-on collision between a car and a speeding truck, resulting in the deaths of seven family members, including three children. Two others were injured in the accident. The truck, loaded with cement, was overtaking recklessly when it collided with the car on the Hanumangarh-Sardarshahar highway late Saturday night. The family was returning from a birthday party and the crash occurred just four kilometers before reaching their home in Naurangdesar. The truck driver fled the scene after the collision.

The severity of the crash led to the front portion of the car being completely mangled, requiring assistance from locals to extricate the victims. Gurbachan Singh Majbi, the bedridden family patriarch who did not attend the party, lost his wife and children in the accident, leaving only a grandson and granddaughter alive, both of whom are hospitalized. The relatives of the deceased have filed a case against the truck driver, as confirmed by Hanumangarh circle inspector Vedpal Sheoran.

This heartbreaking incident serves as a reminder of the devastating consequences of reckless driving and the importance of road safety measures to prevent such tragedies.
